<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-06T08:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-06T08:35:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/2069: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-06T17:00:00+03:25">December
                                    6, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 6—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1091. Declaration as to Iran was enthusiastically received by group of
                            Cabinet members, deputies, Army leaders, and press representatives to
                            whom Prime Minister announced it yesterday. My 1090, December 5.<note n="58" xml:id="d433fn58">Not printed.</note> Deputy Teheri made
                            fulsome speech in praise of Allied chiefs, thanking them for this
                            demonstration of friendship and respect for Iran. Today’s Tehran papers
                            unanimously echo this enthusiasm.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>